Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce (except green beans).

Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{}
with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, @Tuscan Heat Spice{1/2%tsp},
@salt, and @pepper. Roast on top rack until golden and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1 tsp Tuscan Heat Spice.

While potatoes roast, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over
with @Tuscan Heat Spice{1/2%tsp}, @salt, and @pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick,
#pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked
through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; remove chicken from pan.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1 tsp Tuscan Heat Spice.
> TIP: Lower heat if chicken starts to burn.

While chicken cooks, zest @Lemon{1} until you have ¼ tsp; quarter lemon.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, half the
@Balsamic Glaze{2.5%teaspoon}, and ¼ cup @water{1/4%cup}.

> 4 SERVINGS: Zest lemon until you have ½ tsp. Use all the balsamic glaze and
> add 1/3 cup water.

Add balsamic glaze mixture to pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Simmer
until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt and
@pepper.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 TBSP butter.

Pierce @Green Beans{6%ounce} bag with a #fork; place bag on a #plate. Microwave
until tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Carefully transfer beans to a large #bowl. Toss with @Butter{1%tablespoon},
lemon zest, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with @salt and @pepper.

> TIP: No microwave? No problem! Steam beans in a small #pot with a splash of
> water until just tender, 5-7 minutes.

Divide chicken, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Drizzle chicken with
glaze. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.